    "body": "Had an idea over the weekend on how to fix the performance issue of `--source-dir`!\r\n\r\nAfter #1305 most of the profile time of `--source-dir` was spent on walkdir iterating through the whole source tree. It wasn't really possible to improve the performance of the walkdir call, as `map_partial_path` requires us to walk through every file in the source directory (to find files named the same as one of the covered files).\r\n\r\nThe only option left was to not do the walkdir at all, without breaking `map_partial_path`. The idea I had is that calls to `map_partial_path` actually do anything only if one of the covered paths is not a direct child of the source dir. So, if we check that all covered paths exists, we can skip the walkdir altogether!\r\n\r\nOn my coverage file / source tree, this brought processing time from 2.8s to 0.190s, which is more than acceptable :D",
